\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'93Antenor,\uc0\u8232 I\'92m not pleased with what you\'92ve said.\u8232 You know very well how to think up\u8232 some alternative, some better plan.\u8232 But if you truly mean what you\'92ve just said,\u8232 the gods themselves have muddled up your wits.\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0420\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0[360]\u8232 Now I\'92ll speak to horse-taming Trojans.\u8232 I flatly refuse. I won\'92t give up my wife.\u8232 But I will surrender all the goods\u8232 I carried back from Argos to our home.\u8232 I\'92m willing to give up all of it,\u8232 even to add to it things of my own.\'94\
