\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'93Listen to me, Trojans, Dardan allies,\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0430\uc0\u8232 so I may state what the heart in my chest prompts.\u8232 You should prepare your dinner and then eat,\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0[370]\u8232 here in the city, as before. But remember\'97\u8232 keep sentries posted. Each man should stay awake.\u8232 Tomorrow morning Idaios should go\u8232 to the hollow ships, to tell the sons of Atreus,\u8232 both Agamemnon and Menelaus,\u8232 what Alexander has just now proposed,\u8232 the very man whose cause launched this dispute.\u8232 Idaios should propose this wise suggestion\'97\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0440\u8232 if they\'92ll consent to postpone grim warfare,\u8232 so we can burn our dead, we\'92ll fight later,\u8232 until god adjudicates between us\u8232 and awards one side the victory.\'94\
