\'93Son of Atreus, other Achaean leaders,\uc0\u8232 Priam and other noble Trojans asked me\u8232 to tell you what Alexander has proposed,\u8232 if that meets with your approval, an offer\u8232 you will want to hear. That man began our strife.\u8232 All the property which Paris brought here\u8232 in his hollow ships to Troy\'97how I wish\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0[390]\u8232 he\'92d died before that day!\'97he\'92ll hand over\u8232 and add more goods from his own home.\u8232 But he says he\'92ll not return that noble lady,\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0460\u8232 wife of Menelaus, though the Trojans wish\u8232 he\'92d do that. There\'92s more. My orders tell me\u8232 to speak to you to see if you are willing\u8232 to put a stop to the harsh clash of war,\u8232 until such time as we have burned our dead.\u8232 We will fight later, until god chooses\u8232 between us, makes one of us the victors.\'94\
